<br>
Someone with some degree indicated it's a bit heriditary - you'll either be at risk for RSI with your wrists, or you won't.  I don't have it yet, I just get pain in my joints, something completely separate.<br>
<br>
Now to open up the question which always gets flames going... is the use of macros as prevention of RSI's acceptable?<br>
<br>
(( for those less acquainted with videogame and computer terms, macros are programs which automate repetitive actions with the keyboard/mouse, such as tradeskills, bardic twisting... etc. )) <p>~Falcolas Swiftsong~ Virtuoso<br>
